<subSubSection pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
This genus lives at high altitudes on Kilimanjaro and Mount Elgon. 
<taxonomicName genus="Sjostedtinia" lsidName="Sjostedtinia montivaga" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="montivaga">Sjostedtinia montivaga</taxonomicName>
has been collected from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Lobelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lobelia deckeni" order="Asterales" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="deckeni">Lobelia deckeni</taxonomicName>
(Asch.) Hemsl. (
<taxonomicName genus="Lobeliaceae" lsidName="Lobeliaceae" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" rank="genus">Lobeliaceae</taxonomicName>
) (Weise, 1910a), and 
<taxonomicName genus="Sjostedtinia" lsidName="Sjostedtinia fordi" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="fordi">Sjostedtinia fordi</taxonomicName>
Bryant, 1953 from a 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Senecio" order="Asterales" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Senecio</taxonomicName>
sp. (
<taxonomicName genus="Asteraceae" lsidName="Asteraceae" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" rank="genus">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
) in Uganda (Bryant, 1953), and from a 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Lobelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lobelia" order="Asterales" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Lobelia</taxonomicName>
sp. in Kenya (S. Zoia 2009, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
